			"updated_at": "2026-04-29T01:50:04Z",
			"body": "> > when use --profile \"data\\profile\" to run joplin, and write a note with \"$1$\", it will display \"11\" at right side, because the stylesheet will be link to \"resources/app.asar/gui/note-viewer/data/profile/\" but not \"data/profile/\", this pr will fix it.\r\n> \r\n> yes it only supports absolute paths. So why not use an absolute path?\r\n\r\ni want use joplin portably, so i put it into USB drive, anf found it not truly portable on Windows. And then i found this: https://discourse.joplinapp.org/t/tentative-procedure-to-make-joplin-portable-truly-portable-on-windows/39164. it's a good solution basically, but i need to change my \"run.bat\" to use joplin in different computer, because not all USB drive have same drive letter in different computer, using relative path is an easy way.",
